I have Started to learn some of the cool git commands in MAC

-- I checked whether i have my git installed in my folder :
 git --version in my terminal if not install it using brew install git

-- I you have many git hub accounts configure which one you want to use :
    git config --global user.name "Your Name"
    git config --global user.email "your_email@example.com"

-- Navigate to your project folder 
    cd /path/to/your/project
    I used cd /documents/Git Tutorial


--> First command git init
you could be able to see something like this
Reinitialized existing Git repository in /Users/xxx/Documents/GitTutorial/.git/